<subSubSection box="[199,1329,1051,1078]" pageId="16" pageNumber="358" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,223,1221]" box="[199,1329,1051,1078]" pageId="16" pageNumber="358">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,1051,1077]" pageId="16" pageNumber="358">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific epithet refers to the 
<collectingCountry box="[710,874,1051,1078]" name="Vanuatu" pageId="16" pageNumber="358">New Hebrides</collectingCountry>
, the pre-independence name of 
<collectingCountry box="[1230,1326,1052,1078]" name="Vanuatu" pageId="16" pageNumber="358">Vanuatu</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="358" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,223,1221]" pageId="16" pageNumber="358">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1087,1113]" pageId="16" pageNumber="358">Remarks.</emphasis>
A relatively dull and dusted species. In the general shape of the epandrium it shows some affinities to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="MacGowan" authorityYear="2021" box="[180,331,1123,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Lonchaeidae" genus="Silba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erromango">
<emphasis box="[180,331,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="358">S. erromango</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
described above but there are fewer prensisetae. It also lacks the numerous processes arising from the hypandrial structures and the phallus is more complex. The 
<typeStatus box="[856,960,1159,1185]" pageId="16" pageNumber="358">Holotype</typeStatus>
is mounted on a rather large pin which has somewhat squashed the specimen.
</paragraph>
